Name: Install 4G Module on Telecom Relay Mast
Description: How to install a new 4G LTE module in the technical closet, next to a telecom relay mast.

Pages.Name: Preparation
Pages.Description: How to prepare the site for installation.

Steps.Name: Turn off and lock out electrical power
Steps.Description: Make sure you turn off electrical power to the router. Leave the power cable plugged in, to maintain the earth connection. Warning, before performing any of the following procedures, ensure that power is removed from the DC circuit. To ensure that all power is OFF, locate the circuit breaker on the panel board that services the DC circuit. Switch the circuit breaker to the OFF position and tape the switch in place.

Steps.Name: Remove All Network and Telephone Cables
Steps.Description: To prevent damage to the interface card, turn off the electrical power and disconnect the network cables from the chassis, before inserting an interface card into an installed network module or router slot.

Steps.Name: Prepare the Slot
Steps.Description: Prepare the slot for the interface card form factor you are installing. Remove the blank faceplates that are installed over the slot you intend to use. Save the blank faceplates for future use.

Pages.Name: Installation
Pages.Description: Installing the card into the rack.

Steps.Name: Align and Slide the Card
Steps.Description: Align the interface card with the guides in the chassis walls or slot divider and slide it gently into the slot. Do NOT touch the interface card board. Handle the interface card by the edges of the faceplate, to reduce the risk of damage to the card.

Steps.Name: Push Interface Card Home
Steps.Description: Using the faceplate, push the interface card into place until you feel the edge connector seat securely into the connector on the router backplane. The interface card faceplate should touch the chassis rear panel.

Steps.Name: Secure the Card
Steps.Description: Using a number 1 Phillips or flat-blade screwdriver, tighten the captive mounting screws on the interface card faceplate.

Steps.Name: Connect the Card
Steps.Description: Proceed with connecting the interface card to the network, and reconnecting the network cabling.

Pages.Name: Commissioning
Pages.Description: Powering up and checking the installation.

Steps.Name: Reconnecting the Power
Steps.Description: Reconnect the DC power supply. Warning, after wiring the DC power supply, remove the tape from the circuit breaker switch and reinstate the power, by moving the lever to the ON position.

Steps.Name: Turn on the Power to the Router
Steps.Description: Turn on the power to the router using the switch indicated in the picture.

Steps.Name: Verify the Installation of the Interface Card
Steps.Description: Use LED status to verify the Interface Card installation: Blinks green while the card is booting up.  Solid green after the power - on slef test is complete, and the card is operating correctly.

Steps.Name: Tidy up
Steps.Description: Ensure all tools are removed from site. Dispose of all packaging materials and other trash. Notify security that the area is now clear.
